<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 6: CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND
        SLEEVES - ASSEMBLY - CYLINDER SLEEVES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>CYLINDER SLEEVES</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the O-Rings with clean engine oil and install into cylinder sleeve groove
                    (without twist). Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600644">6.44</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Each cylinder sleeve uses two (2) O-Rings.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If required, assure the proper shim(s) is installed, in the crankcase counterbore, so
                    cylinder sleeve protrusion is within specifications. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">"CYLINDER SLEEVE FITTING PROCEDURE"</emph>, (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure 6.39</emph>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Be sure the O-Rings are properly aligned in the groove.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply clean engine oil to the lower crankcase counterbore, then carefully install
                    cylinder sleeve. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600645">6.45</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . If reusing sleeve, rotate 90&#176; from its original position and install in the same bore from
                    which it was removed. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600646">6.46</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After installation, check cylinder sleeve protrusion. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">"Reconditioning"</emph>
                    in this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check cylinder sleeve bore dimensions and sleeve taper per specifications. If the sleeve
                    is not measuring up to specifications, check for improperly aligned O-Rings.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600644" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5346" filename="../figeg5/EG5346.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.44 Lubricate Cylinder Sleeve and Rings</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600645" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5345" filename="../figeg5/EG5345.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.45 Lubricate Cylinder Sleeve Bore</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600646" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg7219" filename="../figeg7/EG7219.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.46 Install Cylinder Sleeve</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
